Coyle Public Schools
April 17, 2018 at 11:56 AM ·

Two elementary students in Coyle Schools lost their home to a fire last night, April 16th. The family lost everything. The students are a girl in 3rd grade and a boy in 5th grade. Coyle Schools will set up a donation station in the superintendent’s office, if anyone would like to donate clothing, shoes, or money to the family.

Sizes for the family:
Girl student size 9 (shoe size 1.5)
Boy student size 12 (shoe size 5)
Mom size 2X shirt
Dad size large shirt
Men's jeans size 30x32

Coyle Public Schools
700 S. Cottingham Ave.
P.O. Box 287
Coyle, OK 73027
School Phone: 405-466-2242
Supt. FAX: 405-466-2448
HS FAX: 405-466-9117

Interest in playing, please call Julie Weathers at 405-202-7915 (cell) and Coyle alumni basketball games this Saturday at new gym. Coyle women’s alumni game starts at 6:30 p.m. followed by men’s alumni games at Coyle new gym. Funds raised go to help the Wayne Gross Memorial Scholarship for a Coyle Senior. 🏀🏀🏀

October 1, 2016 at 10:30 PM · Guthrie, OK ·

Early this morning, the Coyle PTA and volunteers worked on hanging new basketball rims, painting the poles around the baseball field, painting bleachers on the football field, staining/sealing tables for outdoor classroom, but much more needs to be finished! Please join the PTA tomorrow at 2:00 pm to help finish a few more projects, because out kids come first!
